Behaviour Expectations

Team members can:

Add new tasks
Update status, effort, % completion
Add time‑based progress notes


Updates should feel quick and low effort
System should prevent obvious gaps (e.g. closed task with no end date)


Tab 2: Team Overview (For Leads & Managers)
This tab is read‑only for most users and used for reviews, stand-ups, and reporting.
Purpose
Provide a clear, high-level picture of the team’s workload and progress.
Business Views Needed

All tasks in one place
Filters by:

Owner
Status
Platform / Area
Date ranges


Clear visibility of:

What’s in progress
What’s blocked or queued
Recently completed work
Long-running tasks


Easy to answer:

“Who is working on what?”
“How much effort is being spent?”
“What isn’t moving?”



Key Principle
Leads should not need to chase people or open Excel to understand status.

Tab 3: Team Management
This tab is for basic admin or lead usage.
Purpose
Maintain a clean, consistent list of people involved in the work.
